The paper discusses a variation of cuckoo hashing that addresses the issue of multiple lookups in settings where memory is arranged in large pages. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to cuckoo hashing that involves multiple cell choices on a single page and a backup page, which could be relevant to the Databases (cs.DB) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also presents experimental results and suggests new theoretical questions, which could be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
